- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the communication infrastructure and its ability to support UAV operations. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper deals with autonomous UAV systems. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper discusses the control and coordination of UAVs with the assistance of infrastructure. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper mentions the use of edge servers for compute-intense tasks, which could involve AI algorithms. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper may touch upon security concerns related to UAV communication and data transfer.
